50|$|The spotted palm thrush (<b>Cichladusa</b> <b>guttata),</b> {{also known}} as the spotted morning-thrush, is a species of bird in the family Muscicapidae. It is found in Ethiopia, Kenya, Somalia, Sudan, Tanzania, and Uganda. Its natural {{habitats}} are subtropical or tropical dry forests, dry savanna, and subtropical or tropical moist shrubland.|$|E
